WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.280 --> 00:00:02.222
Hey, good morning family!

00:00:02.708 --> 00:00:06.120
We are excited to be with you all again today.

00:00:06.120 --> 00:00:08.400
Boy, we have some stuff to talk to you about.

00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:09.200
We're excited.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:17.420
We'll get to the prayer in a minute, but we have some amazing news to talk about what the Lord is doing.

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:24.015
We went to a healing service again tonight, and the Shekinah of Glory was there.

00:00:24.431 --> 00:00:33.611
I'm telling you all, you know there's people who say, 'Well, we don't have time to drive to go to a certain service or be a part of a revival.

00:00:33.611 --> 00:00:36.160
' How desperate, how hungry are you?

00:00:36.160 --> 00:00:40.746
I'm not criticizing you; I'm trying to say, folks, it's time to get hungry.

00:00:40.746 --> 00:00:42.594
The King is coming!

00:00:42.594 --> 00:00:44.615
The King is coming!

00:00:45.505 --> 00:00:52.173
In this little town of Eufaula, Oklahoma, the glory at the Lighthouse Church is—is it the Lighthouse Church?

00:00:53.759 --> 00:00:55.253
Yeah, I think that's what it's called.

00:00:55.253 --> 00:00:59.135
Precious people there at this church, precious men and women of God.

00:00:59.135 --> 00:01:07.030
The pastors there, the associate pastor and the main pastor, are amazing people—really, really awesome men and women of God.

00:01:07.030 --> 00:01:10.550
And the daughter-in-law, she sings like a bird, man.

00:01:10.550 --> 00:01:15.914
She could bring down the glory with her voice, and it was amazing.

00:01:15.914 --> 00:01:34.644
But they have Billy Burke there, and I'm going to do this without crying, but I'm going to tell you all this: two nights in a row, I've gotten a touch from the Lord that will forever change us both.

00:01:34.644 --> 00:01:48.742
I would encourage you, if Billy Burke is ever in your area, wherever you live, if you look at his itinerary, just try to go to at least one or two of his meetings and bless him.

00:01:48.742 --> 00:01:52.567
Bless him when you go; he is good ground.

00:01:55.832 --> 00:02:22.376
I believe with all my heart—like Diana, I wish I could give more because when you see people's lives being changed by the glory—people that are broken, suicidal, and just ready to give up on life—and you see the presence of God change them.

00:02:22.376 --> 00:02:41.120
You see their countenance when they come up there so heavy and burdened down, just ready to give up, and then when the power of God knocks them down and they get up, their face looks different.

00:02:44.770 --> 00:02:47.133
The demonic spirits lifted off of them.

00:02:47.133 --> 00:02:54.964
So many people we have seen in the last two days have a radical visitation from the Lord.

00:02:54.964 --> 00:03:04.860
Tonight, after last night, I felt like I was being a pig because I got a touch last night.

00:03:04.860 --> 00:03:20.816
Diana said, because we have our own needs, we went up and had Megan prayed for, but we didn't talk about the stuff that we were believing for.

00:03:26.977 --> 00:03:29.285
So Diana said, 'Brandon, why don't we go down to the front?

00:03:29.285 --> 00:03:36.311
' and I said, 'Well, shouldn't we let all the other people get ministered to?

00:03:36.311 --> 00:03:39.295
' But the Lord said, 'Go.

00:03:39.295 --> 00:03:45.230
It's okay to be greedy when it comes to My presence.

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:50.031
' I'm hungry, and when you hunger and thirst after righteousness, He said He'd fill you.

00:03:59.204 --> 00:03:59.369
I told her, 'Come on, babe,' so I grabbed her hand and we ran up to the front.

00:03:59.369 --> 00:04:05.399
Bren watched Megan and made sure she was okay while we went up there and got prayed for.

00:04:06.146 --> 00:04:19.422
The moment we hit the line—we were at the back of the line—it doesn't matter where you are in the line; He meets you where you are.

00:04:19.422 --> 00:04:22.498
You don't have to wait.

00:04:22.498 --> 00:04:30.300
You don't even have to have hands laid on you; He meets you where your faith is.

00:04:40.616 --> 00:04:40.944
We got up and it was almost over, and we thought that he was closing.

00:04:40.944 --> 00:04:45.969
We were like, 'You know, we're just going to go.

00:04:45.969 --> 00:05:02.609
' So we went down there, and we were at the back of the line at the very end of the service, and the tangible presence of God hit us so strong.

00:05:06.479 --> 00:05:06.999
I could barely stand up.

00:05:13.976 --> 00:05:26.489
The glory was all over my legs so much that they were wobbly, and I felt like I was so intoxicated with the Holy Spirit that I was wanting to lean against a wall.

00:05:27.959 --> 00:05:33.743
The closer we got to the front of the altar, the presence of the Lord—I started sweating.

00:05:44.290 --> 00:05:44.633
She couldn't stand; I had to hold her up with my shoulder.

00:05:44.633 --> 00:05:52.680
She was holding on to me so she wouldn't fall out, and I was bracing myself.

00:05:52.680 --> 00:06:03.224
All of a sudden, when we got to him and he said, 'What is wrong?

00:06:03.224 --> 00:06:13.011
' and he prayed for us, the glory of the Lord hit me so strong.

00:06:13.011 --> 00:06:20.199
He said, 'It's the Shekinah of Glory on y'all,' and he said, 'Watch me.

00:06:20.199 --> 00:06:22.510
' He touched me—bam!

00:06:25.102 --> 00:06:25.674
—and I hit the ground.

00:06:25.674 --> 00:06:38.818
I'm telling you, when I did, I felt the presence of the Lord just hit me like a wave, and it hit Diana.

00:06:38.818 --> 00:06:43.240
Oh, I've never felt it that strong in my entire life!

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:46.851
I was just weeping, 'Thank You, Jesus.

00:06:46.851 --> 00:06:50.688
' But this is the part...

00:06:50.688 --> 00:06:55.373
we're going to rewind a little bit here.

00:06:55.951 --> 00:07:16.719
I went to the store today to get her some coats and stuff for the winter so that we'd have some nice clothes for her to wear on these videos and when we go out to these meetings that the Lord's telling us to go to.

00:07:16.719 --> 00:07:25.244
I said, 'Hey babe, you asked for some perfume, let me go ahead and buy you some.

00:07:25.244 --> 00:07:33.462
' I'm glad you like it because it was a treat.

00:07:33.462 --> 00:07:46.780
So I got her this bottle of perfume, and she said, 'Man, Brandon, it smells so lovely.

00:07:51.164 --> 00:07:51.639
I love this.

00:07:51.639 --> 00:07:53.075
This is really nice.

00:07:53.075 --> 00:07:58.764
' I surprised her, and then what did the Lord say to you?

00:07:58.764 --> 00:08:01.335
What did you say?

00:08:01.335 --> 00:08:11.870
Well, I was thinking whenever we were driving in the car, I was thinking about how last night I had had a visitation from the Lord.

00:08:16.942 --> 00:08:18.879
I smelled a campfire when I was just folding laundry.

00:08:32.414 --> 00:08:32.719
We were listening to 'Fire, Fire, Shut Up in My Bones.

00:08:32.719 --> 00:08:44.508
' I was listening to that on the TV; I had the Autumn Assembly of Prayer on our TV from years ago.

00:08:56.565 --> 00:08:56.930
They were praying 'Fire, fire, fire shut up in my bones!

00:08:56.930 --> 00:09:09.240
' Lynn Hammond was preaching, and I was just folding laundry, but I was sucked into it.

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:19.250
I was listening and soaking it in, and it was like I was there.

00:09:29.132 --> 00:09:29.515
I forgot I was even folding laundry; I was just doing it robotically.

00:09:29.515 --> 00:09:36.240
All of a sudden, I smelled a campfire.

00:09:36.827 --> 00:09:39.804
I asked Bren, 'Do you smell that?

00:09:39.804 --> 00:09:46.316
' and he goes, 'No, Mom, I don't smell anything.

00:09:46.316 --> 00:09:50.342
' I said, 'It is so strong.

00:09:51.131 --> 00:09:56.680
Is there a fire going on in this house?

00:09:56.680 --> 00:10:06.286
' We looked around, and I said, 'It's just right here.

00:10:06.286 --> 00:10:13.896
' We found out that it was just right where I was standing that I smelled it.

00:10:13.896 --> 00:10:22.687
Bren came and stood right by me, and he's like, 'Mom, I don't smell anything.

00:10:22.687 --> 00:10:27.720
' I said, 'It's the Holy Spirit.

00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:29.454
I feel His presence here.

00:10:29.454 --> 00:10:38.399
' So, all of a sudden, I just felt His presence on me, and I just hit the floor.

00:10:44.069 --> 00:10:52.206
I was just on my face before God in intercessory prayer, just travailing and travailing.

00:10:52.206 --> 00:11:01.468
After it was over, I went back to where the laundry was and I picked up the laundry and smelled it.

00:11:01.468 --> 00:11:06.760
Bren goes, 'No, the clothes don't smell.

00:11:06.760 --> 00:11:36.586
' I said, 'I know the clothes don't smell because I just got them out of the dryer,' but I've never been around a campfire where it doesn't permeate the clothes.

00:11:41.413 --> 00:11:48.140
I just wanted to see if His presence permeated those clothes, but they didn't smell like anything.

00:12:05.502 --> 00:12:05.976
So I forgot about it, and the next day he gave me the perfume.

00:12:05.976 --> 00:12:20.480
We were driving down there, and I was just looking out the window, talking to God in my heart.

00:12:24.919 --> 00:12:25.559
I said, 'Oh, I like my perfume, Lord.

00:12:25.559 --> 00:12:33.264
' I saw all the flowers outside and said, 'They're so beautiful, Lord.

00:12:33.264 --> 00:12:35.555
I love the way flowers smell.

00:12:35.555 --> 00:12:46.140
' Then I was also thinking about fragrances in general, and I was thinking about last night.

00:12:51.811 --> 00:12:52.137
I was thinking about when his it passed.

00:12:53.114 --> 00:13:09.954
When he first passed, his grandma would take his clothes and she would breathe them in because she wanted to smell it because she missed him so much.

00:13:11.018 --> 00:13:19.146
I remember when she said, 'His fragrance is even leaving the clothes.

00:13:19.146 --> 00:13:36.790
' After a couple of weeks, his scent started wearing off his old clothes, and she was crying.

00:13:38.440 --> 00:13:47.680
I heard the Lord say to me, 'Diana,' because I was thinking about those clothes and I wondered why they didn't smell like that.

00:13:48.338 --> 00:13:49.160
It was so tangible, Lord.

00:13:50.960 --> 00:14:03.120
And He said, 'Diana, the fragrances don't last very long because when you take a flower and put it in a vase, even the fragrance from a rose dies.

00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:08.501
It doesn't smell very good forever because it's separated from its source.

00:14:08.501 --> 00:14:14.434
' It hit me, and He said, 'Diana, I smell so good.

00:14:28.907 --> 00:14:29.204
My fragrance is amazing.

00:14:29.204 --> 00:14:34.246
' I said, 'Oh, Father, I bet it is.

00:14:34.246 --> 00:14:45.389
' Then when we got there in that line, at the back of the line, I started smelling this fragrance.

00:14:57.440 --> 00:14:57.591
It was the most beautiful fragrance I've ever smelled.

00:14:57.591 --> 00:15:00.939
When you breathed it in, it was like life.

00:15:01.299 --> 00:15:03.759
I felt the Holy Spirit say, 'Breathe.

00:15:03.759 --> 00:15:10.276
' The more I breathed, the more I could hardly stand.

00:15:10.276 --> 00:15:15.654
I was like, 'Guys, Heaven's going to smell so good!

00:15:15.654 --> 00:15:19.639
' I was standing next to her, and she said, 'Brandon, do you not smell it?

00:15:19.639 --> 00:15:26.418
' At the time, I didn't smell anything.

00:15:28.880 --> 00:15:52.100
When she said, 'Brandon, just breathe,' I took a deep breath and the fragrance went all through my nose and down my throat.

00:15:56.351 --> 00:15:57.529
I said, 'Oh, I smell it too, babe!

00:15:57.529 --> 00:16:03.800
' It smelled to me like honeysuckle.

00:16:03.800 --> 00:16:09.896
The fragrance was so beautiful, like roses, like beautiful flowers.

00:16:09.896 --> 00:16:16.885
Even before, when I've smelled the Lord, I said it's like frankincense.

00:16:19.084 --> 00:16:22.347
It's a very beautiful smell, like anointing oil.

00:16:22.347 --> 00:16:34.511
But this, I can tell you all, there's nothing on this earth I've ever smelled like the Shekinah Glory.

00:16:36.458 --> 00:16:43.420
The tangible presence of the Lord has an odor, and it was so strong at that altar.

00:16:43.420 --> 00:16:49.102
I was trying to think, 'Who smells like this?

00:16:49.102 --> 00:16:57.719
' I wanted to sniff people because I was like, 'Where is—who's the source?

00:17:00.587 --> 00:17:01.253
This is beautiful!

00:17:01.253 --> 00:17:07.109
' You couldn't get enough of it.

00:17:18.040 --> 00:17:18.260
I breathed it in again, and it got even stronger.

00:17:18.260 --> 00:17:27.429
Whenever he touched me and the power of God hit me, I laid on the ground and I couldn't get up.

00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:40.040
I literally felt like I had cement glue gluing me to the ground.

00:17:41.320 --> 00:17:56.749
I just sat there and looked at the lights because I could not move off the floor.

00:17:58.039 --> 00:18:01.871
I thought, 'Well, what do we do now?

00:18:01.871 --> 00:18:11.051
' so I just laid there and balled because the Lord was just touching me.

00:18:20.891 --> 00:18:23.309
I got up off the floor—I'm so drunk with the Holy Spirit—I scooted my body up against the wall of the altar and smelled that fragrance again.

00:18:23.309 --> 00:18:30.850
I carried her out on my arm because she was so drunk in the Holy Spirit.

00:18:30.850 --> 00:18:41.550
I put her in the car, and almost the whole way home I could get whiffs of it.

00:18:41.550 --> 00:18:54.467
But the more I drove and focused on the road, I didn't smell it anymore, but she could smell it the whole way home.

00:18:54.467 --> 00:18:58.332
Then my kids started to smell it.

00:19:17.476 --> 00:19:17.778
I was like, 'Please don't leave!

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:22.280
I want to smell this forever.

00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:35.461
' God's a good God, y'all, and He wants good things for His kids.

00:19:35.461 --> 00:19:41.611
When we get to heaven, what a day of rejoicing that will be!

00:19:41.611 --> 00:19:44.355
We'll sing and shout the victory!

00:19:55.520 --> 00:19:55.698
It's going to be awesome.

00:19:55.698 --> 00:19:59.087
But He's coming; the King is coming.

00:20:03.978 --> 00:20:19.590
I haven't been able to really talk about the experience we had with Him two or three nights ago when He came just loving on us and gave us a word about what's coming.

00:20:19.590 --> 00:20:26.296
He knows exactly what each and every one of us needs.

00:20:26.296 --> 00:20:27.760
It's so custom-fit.

00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:36.180
He knows the number of hairs on your head.

00:20:36.180 --> 00:20:41.808
He knows what every single one of us needs.

00:20:54.125 --> 00:20:54.668
It's not just a cookie-cutter thing; He does it custom just for you.

00:21:04.426 --> 00:21:06.310
The words that we've been given this week from Nancy and Billy were all things Jesus spoke to us as confirmation.

00:21:07.573 --> 00:21:14.764
I told her, 'If I said this publicly, people are going to say we're bragging.

00:21:14.764 --> 00:21:31.880
' So when the man of God hears the Holy Spirit say what Jesus said in our house and he starts confirming things, I just sit there and go, 'Wow.

00:21:31.880 --> 00:21:36.060
' Folks, what a mighty God we serve!

00:21:41.910 --> 00:21:52.792
I would encourage everybody, if you see Billy Burke's itinerary and he is in your area, do whatever you can to be there and support this man.

00:21:52.792 --> 00:21:55.304
Help him; God is using him.

00:21:55.304 --> 00:21:57.960
People say, 'Well, that's all fake.

00:21:57.960 --> 00:22:00.074
' You are missing it.

00:22:00.074 --> 00:22:24.999
I'm going to tell you this: if you say, 'I don't believe in the healings, I think all that's fake, all those people make up random crap out of their mouth,' the tangible presence of the Lord there is enough in itself to go out and seek it.

00:22:24.999 --> 00:22:43.410
If there were no healings or manifestations of God's power, just the presence in the service alone would be enough because the Holy Spirit was there so strong.

00:22:43.410 --> 00:22:55.468
Folks, you are dry and thirsty; find a well and drink from the well that never shall run dry.

00:22:55.468 --> 00:23:02.200
'Fill my cup, Lord; I lift it up, Lord.

00:23:02.200 --> 00:23:05.960
Come and quench this thirsting of my soul.

00:23:05.960 --> 00:23:10.534
Bread of Heaven, feed me till I want no more.

00:23:10.534 --> 00:23:18.107
' We told her, we can be like roadies, man!

00:23:18.107 --> 00:23:33.311
We can follow the band out; we'll follow Billy Burke around and just see who gets healed in his services just for fun.

00:23:34.689 --> 00:23:48.044
I have more enjoyment out of seeing who gets their life changed and being a part of something bigger than yourself than anything else in life.

00:23:48.044 --> 00:23:56.314
Who wants to sit home and be bored watching TV on the couch?

00:23:56.314 --> 00:23:59.520
We don't live a boring life, folks.

00:23:59.520 --> 00:24:05.039
We walk in the supernatural because we're hungry for it.

00:24:05.039 --> 00:24:12.860
We're always watching services to sharpen ourselves, to grow from glory to glory.

00:24:12.860 --> 00:24:14.831
We're continually feeding and feeding.

00:24:14.831 --> 00:24:17.715
That's the way we live our life.

00:24:17.715 --> 00:24:22.960
We're reading John's book right now, Awe of God.

00:24:22.960 --> 00:24:32.245
It's a phenomenal book—probably a top 10 best book I've ever had Diana read to me.

00:24:35.009 --> 00:24:36.022
The Awe of God by John Bevere, folks, it's amazing.

00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:40.120
I think everybody should read it; it's life-changing.

00:24:41.820 --> 00:25:04.428
In fact, I would love to meet him just to pick his brain, to have him on our channel to talk about Awe of God and what inspired him to write that book.

00:25:04.428 --> 00:25:14.960
I know the Holy Spirit did, but where did that knowledge and fear that he's walking in come from?

00:25:25.490 --> 00:25:25.780
That revelation knowledge of the Lord—you don't hear people talking that way.

00:25:25.780 --> 00:25:31.559
When you read that book, the revelation that he has...

00:25:31.559 --> 00:25:37.813
please read the book, Awe of God by John Bevere.

00:25:46.256 --> 00:25:46.468
It will change your life.

00:25:46.468 --> 00:25:52.870
I tell her, 'Babe, how do you find these books?

00:25:52.870 --> 00:26:02.577
' She has a gift; the Holy Spirit will guide her and say, 'This is what Brandon needs to hear.

00:26:02.577 --> 00:26:09.012
' I just love John Bevere and Lisa Bevere.

00:26:09.012 --> 00:26:15.542
What a blessing they are to the body of Christ.

00:26:24.679 --> 00:26:38.920
Just the revelation of knowing their 'Ephesians moment,' that their eyes of understanding have been enlightened to the Awe of God.

00:26:38.920 --> 00:26:44.502
It is worth a read.

00:26:44.502 --> 00:27:10.589
There are so many avenues you can tap into, whether it's reading a book or the Word—of course, you always should read the Word—but even putting prayer conferences like the Autumn Assembly of Prayer on your TV, having that playing, or worship music.

00:27:10.589 --> 00:27:24.210
If you're seeking Him, the Bible says, 'Seek ye first the kingdom of God and His righteousness, and all these things will be added unto you.

00:27:24.210 --> 00:27:26.742
' He'll meet you halfway.

00:27:26.742 --> 00:27:30.995
But if you're lazy, if you're not hungry...

00:27:36.712 --> 00:27:42.709
I feel like people get spiritually lazy and they're expecting somebody to spoon-feed them like a baby.

00:27:42.709 --> 00:27:45.310
How desperate are you?

00:27:45.310 --> 00:27:52.660
How bad do you want your life to change?

00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:56.480
We don't just listen to anything.

00:27:56.480 --> 00:28:01.579
She skims through books until the Holy Spirit says, 'This one.

00:28:01.579 --> 00:28:10.720
' I encourage you to read that and to find Billy Burke's ministry.

00:28:10.720 --> 00:28:35.080
I know he's around Tampa a lot, Miami sometimes in hotels, and he's going to Las Vegas to do a crusade soon, and California.

00:28:35.080 --> 00:28:50.880
His itinerary is on his website.

00:29:02.336 --> 00:29:44.640
I don't know if he has any more meetings this year, but the first of the year he always does a lot.

00:29:53.360 --> 00:29:58.799
We are just encouraged; I want to tell you all that there is a shifting that has happened.

00:29:58.799 --> 00:30:17.582
A lot of times we say there's a shifting coming in the future; no, there is a shifting that has manifested, and it is tangible.

00:30:26.513 --> 00:30:26.919
I can feel the shifting in the atmosphere.

00:30:26.919 --> 00:30:29.440
There's something different now.

00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:38.343
Once we passed Yom Kippur and entered into that time frame, there's something different.

00:30:38.343 --> 00:30:43.760
It's not the same anymore.

00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:52.537
I'm just anticipating: first the blade, then the ear, then the full manifestation.

00:30:52.537 --> 00:31:01.886
I'm going to go ahead and start leading us in prayer.

00:31:07.559 --> 00:31:07.760
Thank you, babe, for coming on and talking.

00:31:07.760 --> 00:31:08.760
I'm excited.

00:31:08.760 --> 00:31:19.628
I'm going to take communion with them and we're going to finish our prayer thing up.

00:31:19.628 --> 00:31:32.039
I just wanted Diana to come on today and tell you what happened and how we both were so blessed.

00:31:32.039 --> 00:31:35.739
Our kids, everybody was blessed.

00:31:35.739 --> 00:31:38.919
There's power in prayer.

00:31:38.919 --> 00:31:40.485
We're excited!

00:31:40.485 --> 00:31:41.465
We're anticipating!

00:31:41.465 --> 00:31:49.903
All right, so we're going to get to the prayer part of this.

00:31:49.903 --> 00:31:59.271
My wife got me this shirt; it says, 'Make Heaven Crowded.

00:31:59.271 --> 00:32:05.004
' I'm just here recruiting.

00:32:05.004 --> 00:32:07.612
I thought it was cool.

00:32:07.612 --> 00:32:14.227
She got it off Amazon for about 20 bucks.

00:32:14.227 --> 00:32:16.745
'Make Heaven Crowded.

00:32:16.745 --> 00:32:19.880
' For God's glory.

00:32:31.931 --> 00:32:35.006
Father, I thank You for the manifestation of the glory of the Lord over the minds right now.

00:32:44.857 --> 00:32:45.931
In the name of Jesus, we take authority over this demonic oppression from PTSD.

